()Policy kya hai?
--🔐 SailPoint me Policy kya hoti hai? (Hinglish)
SailPoint (IdentityIQ / IdentityNow) me Policy ka matlab hota hai:-
👉 Security rules jo check karte hain ki kisi user ka access sahi hai ya galat (risk ya violation hai ya nahi)

🔹 Simple samajh:-
👉 System check karta hai:-
“User ko jo access mila hai, kya wo allowed hai?”
Agar nahi → ❌ Policy Violation

🔐 SailPoint me kitne type ki Policies hoti hain?
1️⃣ Access Policy:-
👉 Check karta hai ki user ke paas jo access hai wo allowed hai ya nahi

Example:-
User ko admin access nahi milna chahiye

2️⃣ SoD Policy (Segregation of Duties):-
👉 Conflicting roles detect karta hai.
Example:-
"Create Payment" + "Approve Payment" ❌

3️⃣ Password Policy:-
👉 Password rules define karta hai
Example:-
Minimum 8 characters
Special character mandatory

4️⃣ Activity Policy:-
👉 User ke actions monitor karta hai
Example:-
Bahut zyada failed login attempts
Suspicious activity

5️⃣ Risk-Based Policy:-
👉 User ke risk score ke basis pe decision
Example:-
High risk user → access block

6️⃣ Certification Policy (Review Policy)?
👉 Access review ke time check hota hai.
Example:-
Manager verify kare ki employee ka access sahi hai.

🔥 Main Difference: Policy vs PolicyViolation
🔐 1️⃣ Policy (sailpoint.object.Policy):-
👉 Ye rule/configuration hota hai
Define karta hai:-
kya check karna hai
kis condition pe violation hoga
severity kya hogi
👉 Matlab:-
“Rule banane wala object”

🚨 2️⃣ PolicyViolation (sailpoint.object.PolicyViolation):-
👉 Ye result/output hota hai
Jab policy fail hoti hai → ye object create hota hai
Isme hota hai:-
kis user ne violate kiya
kya violation hai
mitigation / resolution kya hai.
👉 Matlab:-
“Rule tootne ka result”
