()🔥 1️⃣ isEnabled() / setEnabled(boolean enabled):-
👉 Kya karta hai?
➡️ Ye system level switch hai
👉 Matlab SailPoint engine decide karta hai:-

Policy ko evaluate karna hai ya ignore karna hai
💡 Simple samajh:-
true → policy chalegi (engine use karega)
false → policy bilkul ignore ho jayegi

📌 Code:-
policy.setEnabled(true);

System.out.println(policy.isEnabled());
✅ Output:-
true

🧠 Real use:-
Temporary disable karna (maintenance, testing)
Policy ko completely band karna
----------
🔥 2️⃣ isActive() / setActive(boolean active):-
👉 Ye batata hai policy currently use me hai ya nahi.

📌 Code:-
policy.setActive(true);

System.out.println(policy.isActive());
-----------
🔥 3️⃣ getState() / setState(String state)
👉 Kya karta hai?
➡️ Ye policy ka lifecycle stage batata hai.

DRAFT        → abhi ban rahi hai
ACTIVE       → live hai
INACTIVE     → use nahi ho rahi
DEPRECATED   → purani ho gayi
📌 Code:-
policy.setState("DRAFT");
System.out.println(policy.getState());
-----------------------------------------
🔥 🔥 Teeno ka Combined Flow:-
Step 1: Policy banayi
        State = DRAFT
        Enabled = false
        Active = false

Step 2: Testing complete
        Enabled = true

Step 3: Go Live
        Active = true
        State = ACTIVE

Step 4: Old ho gayi
        Active = false
        State = DEPRECATED
----------------------------------------------
