///////////////*
()🔥 1️⃣ Resolution (kya hota hai?)
👉 Resolution ka matlab hai problem ko poori tarah solve kar dena (final fix)

✅ Kya karta hai:-
Root cause ko fix karta hai
Issue permanently close kar deta hai

📌 Example:-
User ko galti se Admin access mil gaya
👉 Resolution:-
Admin access remove kar diya
Correct role assign kar diya

🎯 Result:-
✔ Problem completely fix
✔ Future me same issue nahi aayega

⚡ 2️⃣ Mitigation (kya hota hai?)
👉 Mitigation ka matlab hai risk ko temporarily control ya reduce karna.

✅ Kya karta hai:-
Problem ko turant control karta hai
Lekin permanent fix nahi hota

📌 Example:-
User ke paas risky access hai (remove nahi kar sakte immediately)
👉 Mitigation:-
Monitoring enable kar di
Approval mandatory kar diya
Time-based access laga diya

🎯 Result:-
✔ Risk kam ho gaya
❌ Problem fully solve nahi hui
*///////////////
---------------------------------------
✅ getMitigationRequired() / setMitigationRequired(boolean val)
👉 Kya karta hai?

➡️ Ye batata hai:-
Violation ke liye mitigation (temporary control) zaroori hai ya nahi.

🧠 Real use:-
High risk cases me mitigation mandatory
Approval ke bina access allow nahi.
-----------------------------------------------
✅ getMitigationDescription() / setMitigationDescription(String desc)
👉 Kya karta hai?

➡️ Ye batata hai:-
Mitigation kaise karna hai (instructions)

📌 Code:-
policy.setMitigationDescription("Manager approval required for temporary access");

System.out.println(policy.getMitigationDescription());
✅ Output:-
Manager approval required for temporary access

🧠 Real use:-
User / admin ko guide karna
Compliance proof

🔥 🔥 Violation Handling Flow 💥:-
Violation detect hua
        ↓
ViolationOwner assign hua
        ↓
Check: MitigationRequired?
        ↓
Yes → mitigation follow karo
        ↓
Description ke hisab se action lo
----------------------------------------------------
